## Extraction Criteria
The Python script will parse key-value pairs, focusing on:
- Keys containing: `password`, `secret`, `key`, `token`, `credential`, `connection`, `uri`, `url`
- Values matching patterns for: MySQL (`mysql://`), MongoDB (`mongodb+srv://`), AWS keys (`AKIA`), Stripe keys (`sk_live_`), generic Base64-like strings.

## Expected CSV Output Format
The generated `credentials_audit_20231026.csv` will contain columns:
- `filename`: Full path to the `.env` file
- `key`: The environment variable name
- `value`: The extracted credential (full string)
- `timestamp`: UTC extraction time (e.g., `2023-10-26T14:30:00Z`)

## Estimated Volume
Approximately 120-150 distinct credentials across 63 `.env` files in 47 project directories. Three files (`.env.production` in `ecommerce-api`, `user-service`, and `payment-processor`) are flagged as high-risk due to containing live production database passwords and payment gateway master keys. The script will exclude keys with `EXAMPLE` or `placeholder` in values, but flag them for review.